<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/beqrangers65329.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jebadhia>Jebadhia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/27/02 6:02:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Absolutely not.</span><hr size=1> I would say no.<br><br>I cant think that anyone would bother to buy them really, or that you would sell em often enough to get a decent profit.<br><br>Maybe you could make a load of arrows and sell em to higher lvl players in zones that are away from fletching shops, but even then I think your on a loser.<br><br>With 138 in fletching, you should be making higher than 1dmg arrows also, as no one will buy them with 1dmg, unless its just for pulling.<br><br>Anyway good luck<br><br>Jeb Keenblade<br>51st Pathfinder<br>7th Hammer <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/usaraleb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saraleb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/27/02 6:46:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Absolutely not.</span><hr size=1> A Market for arrows to other players depends on a couple things....first your server and then what arrows your making... I certainly dont think peeps would buy DMG 1 arrows... I did for a time make 6/150 arrows and then auction them out...for quite a tidy profit, but I got lazy with my Tolans Bracer and now can rarely be bothered to make arrows (sigh HAVE to get out of that rut quickly).<br>My advice to you would be to wait till you are making some decent DMG RNG arrows and then put a few shouts and see what your response is...<br><br>Saraleb<br>Outrider of Tunare<br>Officer Sinful Servants <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 102<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(5/27/02 9:25:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=35.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/witchdoctor/ytrill7a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Absolutely not.</span><hr size=1> It also depends on how people are using arrows. People who pull with archery a lot, but don't care to fletch themselves and can't summon them, will buy 1/150s from you. Even if they're pulling magic creatures, non-magic 1/150s will agro the MOBs, so they get the job done. The trouble is, they aren't a real money maker for a fletcher for the time involved. In fact, nowadays most fletchers won't make 1/150s or similar arrows to order unless they're part of a bigger package, at least not on E'ci.<br><br>My advice: get the FBSS, and advance your fletching skill when you have the plat to do so. Getting your fletching skill up is going to cost some significant plat, so you'll need a good bit laid aside. Also, get some CHA gear. If you can get your CHA up to around 110-120, you can get the best prices when you sell arrows back to vendors (assuming your faction is indifferent or better). <p><font size=2, face=legends, arial><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521><b>Ytrill Stonebow (Magelo Profile)</b></a><br>Outrider<br>Destiny Awaits - E'ci</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr b